// Test: calling processEvents() inside a callback causes re-entrant dispatch.
// The inner processEvents() calls DispatchPendingEvents() again while the
// outer is mid-iteration. Since FPendingKeys hasn't been cleared yet,
// the inner dispatch re-iterates the same events (double fire).
// The inner call then clears the list, so the outer loop finishes without
// visiting further items.
//
// This documents current (known) behavior. A guard flag could prevent
// re-entrant dispatch, but for now we just verify it doesn't crash.

var pressCount = 0;
var reentrantCalled = false;

onKeyPressed(fun(key) {
  pressCount = pressCount + 1;
  if (!reentrantCalled) {
    reentrantCalled = true;
    processEvents(); // re-entrant — will re-dispatch pending events
  }
});

simulateKeyDown("x");
processEvents();

// "x" fires once in outer, then the re-entrant processEvents re-dispatches
// "x" again (inner). The guard flag prevents infinite recursion.
// Total: 2 fires of onKeyPressed.
print str(pressCount); // expect: 2
